==German==
===Etymology===
Thieve's argot; from ''Stappler'' "[[beggar]]", not related to [[stapeln]]. ''Hochstapler'' means a beggar acting like he is originally high class, but in a dire situation.
===Noun===
'''Hochstapler''' ''m''
# [[conman]], [[con man]], [[impostor]]

